---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Everything you need to know about Tour de Lakewood - a free 12-hour community cycling event through Lakewood, Ohio on July 11th, 2026."
>
  <!-- BLACK HERO -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">Tour de Lakewood &rsaquo; About</p>
      <h1 class="page-h1">
        About<br />
        <em>the Ride</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="page-sub">
        Everything you need to know about Lakewood&rsquo;s 12-hour cycling event -
        no peloton required.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS IT -->
  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose-layout">
        <div class="prose-sidebar">
          <p class="section-tag">The Event</p>
        </div>
        <div class="prose-main">
          <h2 class="section-h2">What is Tour de Lakewood?</h2>
          <p class="prose">
            Tour de Lakewood is a free, community-organized cycling event that takes place
            entirely within the city limits of Lakewood, Ohio. On July 11th, 2026, riders
            of all ages and abilities are invited to explore Lakewood&rsquo;s neighborhoods,
            parks, and streets on two wheels.
          </p>
          <p class="prose">
            Unlike a traditional race or gran fondo, Tour de Lakewood has no mandatory course,
            no required distance, and no entry fee. You choose how long you ride, where you go,
            and what pace you keep. The only requirement is that you enjoy yourself and
            approximately stay within city limits.
          </p>
          <p class="prose">
            Think of it as the Tour de France, except that it's nothing like the Tour de France. It's a fun, casual event for the community.
          </p>
          <p class="prose">
            The first edition took place in 2025 - a small, informal ride with a handful of people, three categories, and more questions than answers. We&rsquo;re still figuring it out as we go. 2026 is the second year, and we&rsquo;re hoping it&rsquo;s bigger and slightly better organized.
          </p>
          <p class="prose">
            Tour de Lakewood is organized in affiliation with <a href="https://www.bikecleveland.org/bikelakewood/" class="prose-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bike Lakewood<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>, the local branch of Bike Cleveland working to make Lakewood a more bikeable city.
          </p>
          <a href="https://www.bikecleveland.org/bikelakewood/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="bike-lkwd-logo-link">
            <img src="https://www.bikecleveland.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bikelkwd-logo-2color-screen-e1508261291246.png" alt="Bike Lakewood" class="bike-lkwd-logo" />
            <span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
  <section class="section section--black">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-tag-light">The Format</p>
      <h2 class="section-h2-light">How it works.</h2>
      <div class="steps-grid">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">01</div>
          <h3 class="step-title">Show up on July 11th</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The event runs 8:00 AM to 8:00 PM Eastern. We'll do a fun ride under 10 miles to start, and then you're on your own.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">02</div>
          <h3 class="step-title">Ride Lakewood your way</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            Choose your own route through the city. Cover as many neighborhoods as you like,
            or stick to your favorite stretch of Detroit. There are no wrong turns,
            except maybe into Lake Erie.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">03</div>
          <h3 class="step-title">Track your mileage</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            Use Strava, Garmin, or any GPS app to record your ride. Then upload your GPX file
            to the Route Analyzer to see how many miles of your ride fell inside Lakewood city
            limits.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">04</div>
          <h3 class="step-title">Check the results</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            After the event, community results are posted on the Results page. Three leaderboards: most total distance, most map coverage (what % of Lakewood you covered), and most elevation gain. Bragging rights guaranteed. We&rsquo;ll also try to have an after party somewhere. Details to come.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO IS IT FOR -->
  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="rider-layout">
        <div class="rider-intro">
          <p class="section-tag">Participation</p>
          <h2 class="section-h2">Who is it for?</h2>
          <p class="prose">
            Tour de Lakewood is open to everyone. You don&rsquo;t need a carbon road bike,
            a heart rate monitor, or a Strava subscription to participate. If you have a
            working bicycle and a few hours to spare, you&rsquo;re in.
          </p>
          <p class="prose">
            Past participants have included families on cruiser bikes, lifelong commuters,
            serious cyclists using the event as a training day, and total beginners on
            borrowed bikes from the garage.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rider-cards">
          <div class="rider-card">
            <h4 class="rider-title">Casual Riders</h4>
            <p class="rider-desc">Ride for an hour or two. Grab a coffee. Enjoy the city. No metrics required.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rider-card">
            <h4 class="rider-title">Commuters</h4>
            <p class="rider-desc">Already know every shortcut? Challenge yourself to discover new streets.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rider-card rider-card--yellow">
            <h4 class="rider-title">Competitive</h4>
            <p class="rider-desc">Log as many Lakewood miles as physically possible in 12 hours. Dominate the leaderboard.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rider-card">
            <h4 class="rider-title">Families</h4>
            <p class="rider-desc">The best excuse for a family bike ride around the neighborhood all year.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EVENT DETAILS -->
  <section class="section section--yellow">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-tag">Event Details</p>
      <h2 class="section-h2">Mark your calendar.</h2>
      <div class="details-grid">
        <div class="detail-item">
          <div class="detail-label">Date</div>
          <div class="detail-value">Saturday, July 11th, 2026</div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-item">
          <div class="detail-label">Time</div>
          <div class="detail-value">8:00 AM &ndash; 8:00 PM Eastern</div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-item">
          <div class="detail-label">Location</div>
          <div class="detail-value">Lakewood, Ohio (city-wide)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-item">
          <div class="detail-label">Cost</div>
          <div class="detail-value">Free to participate</div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-item">
          <div class="detail-label">Equipment</div>
          <div class="detail-value">Any rideable bicycle</div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-item">
          <div class="detail-label">Route</div>
          <div class="detail-value">Self-directed - choose your own path</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RACE DAY SCHEDULE -->
  <section class="section section--black">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-tag-light">July 11, 2026</p>
      <h2 class="section-h2-light">Race Day Schedule.</h2>
      <div class="timeline">

        <div class="tl-item">
          <div class="tl-time">
            <span class="tl-hr">8:00</span>
            <span class="tl-ampm">AM</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tl-connector">
            <div class="tl-dot"></div>
            <div class="tl-line-seg"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="tl-body">
            <h3 class="tl-title">Grand D&eacute;part - Madison Park</h3>
            <p class="tl-desc">
              Kick off the day at Madison Park in Lakewood. We&rsquo;ll do a group
              ride under 10 miles to start - route TBD, will be posted on
              RidewithGPS before the event. After that, the city is yours for the
              next 12 hours.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tl-item">
          <div class="tl-time">
            <span class="tl-hr">2:00</span>
            <span class="tl-ampm">PM</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tl-connector">
            <div class="tl-dot"></div>
            <div class="tl-line-seg"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="tl-body">
            <h3 class="tl-title">Midday Meetup - Lakewood Truck Park</h3>
            <p class="tl-desc">
              Optional mid-ride pit stop for snacks and libations, if you so choose.
              Roll through, refuel, and get back on the road.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tl-item tl-item--last">
          <div class="tl-time">
            <span class="tl-hr">8:00</span>
            <span class="tl-ampm">PM</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tl-connector">
            <div class="tl-dot tl-dot--end"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="tl-body">
            <h3 class="tl-title">Ride Hard Stop - Afterparty at Sauced Taproom &amp; Kitchen</h3>
            <p class="tl-desc">
              Wheels down at 8 PM. Head over to Sauced Taproom and Kitchen on
              Detroit Ave for the official afterparty and race results announcement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-layout">
        <div class="faq-sidebar">
          <p class="section-tag">FAQ</p>
          <h2 class="section-h2">Common<br />questions.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq-q">Do I need to register in advance?</summary>
            <p class="faq-a">
              No registration required. Show up on the day, ride, and that&rsquo;s it.
              Registration details will be posted here as the event approaches.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq-q">Is there a minimum distance I need to ride?</summary>
            <p class="faq-a">
              Absolutely not. Ride one mile or fifty - it&rsquo;s entirely up to you.
              The event is about participation and exploring the city, not hitting a
              specific number.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq-q">What kind of bike do I need?</summary>
            <p class="faq-a">
              Any bike that can safely roll on paved roads. Road bikes, mountain bikes,
              hybrids, e-bikes, cargo bikes - all welcome. Lakewood streets are paved
              and suitable for most tire widths. The most challenging terrain is
              approximately the hill on Edgewater Drive.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq-q">What is the Route Analyzer?</summary>
            <p class="faq-a">
              The Route Analyzer is a tool where you upload a GPX file from your GPS device
              or Strava and it calculates how many miles of your ride fell within Lakewood
              city limits, along with the percentage of the city you covered. Great for
              settling arguments about who actually rode more of Lakewood.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq-q">Can I ride with a group?</summary>
            <p class="faq-a">
              Yes! Ride solo or with friends - whatever you prefer. There are no
              required group starts and no organized group rides, so you have full
              flexibility. Form your own peloton.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq-q">What if it rains?</summary>
            <p class="faq-a">
              The event happens rain or shine. That said, use your judgement - if
              conditions are unsafe, prioritize your safety. Post-event results
              don&rsquo;t require a perfect weather day.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq-q">Is this affiliated with the actual Tour de France?</summary>
            <p class="faq-a">
              Absolutely not. ASO has not been notified. The yellow jersey is symbolic.
              No one is drafting behind a team car on Madison.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .sr-only {
    position: absolute;
    width: 1px;
    height: 1px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: -1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
    white-space: nowrap;
    border: 0;
  }

  .container { max-width: var(--container); margin: 0 auto; }

  /* ---- Hero ---- */
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--purple);
    padding: 4.5rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--yellow);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .page-h1 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(4rem, 10vw, 8rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 0.9;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .page-h1 em { font-style: normal; color: var(--yellow); }

  .page-sub {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #ccc;
    max-width: 34rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Shared section ---- */
  .section { padding: 5.5rem 1.5rem; }
  .section--white { background: var(--white); border-bottom: 1px solid #e8e8e8; }
  .section--black { background: var(--purple); }
  .section--yellow {
    background: var(--yellow-bg);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--yellow-border);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--yellow-border);
  }

  .section-tag {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 0.75rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--yellow);
  }

  .section-tag-light {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: #ccc;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 0.75rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--yellow);
  }

  .section-h2 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .section-h2-light {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
  }

  .prose {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .prose-link {
    color: var(--purple);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .prose-link:hover { color: var(--text); }

  .bike-lkwd-logo-link { display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .bike-lkwd-logo { height: 250px; width: auto; display: block; }

  /* ---- Prose layout ---- */
  .prose-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
    gap: 3.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .prose-sidebar { padding-top: 0.4rem; }

  /* ---- Steps ---- */
  .steps-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    background: #2a2a2a;
    border: 1px solid #2a2a2a;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .step {
    background: #1b1b1b;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .step-num {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--yellow);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .step-title {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .step-desc {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #aaa;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Rider types ---- */
  .rider-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .rider-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .rider-card {
    background: var(--gray-light);
    border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
    border-radius: 0.875rem;
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  .rider-card--yellow {
    background: var(--yellow);
    border-color: var(--yellow-border);
  }

  .rider-card--yellow .rider-title,
  .rider-card--yellow .rider-desc { color: var(--black); }
  .rider-card--yellow .rider-desc { color: #333; }

  .rider-title {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
  }

  .rider-desc {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Details ---- */
  .details-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .detail-item {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--yellow-border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .detail-label {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .detail-value {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  /* ---- FAQ ---- */
  .faq-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .faq-sidebar { position: sticky; top: calc(var(--nav-h) + 2rem); }

  .faq-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.65rem; }

  .faq {
    border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--gray-light);
  }

  .faq-q {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    color: var(--text);
    user-select: none;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-q::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .faq-q::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', sans-serif;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq[open] .faq-q::after { content: '–'; }

  .faq-a {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0 1.25rem 1.1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--card-border);
    padding-top: 1rem;
    background: var(--white);
  }

  /* ---- Timeline ---- */
  .timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    max-width: 660px;
  }

  .tl-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 32px 1fr;
    gap: 0 1.25rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .tl-time {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-end;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  .tl-hr {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.55rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--yellow);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .tl-ampm {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #666;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }

  .tl-connector {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    padding-top: 0.22rem;
  }

  .tl-dot {
    width: 13px;
    height: 13px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--yellow);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .tl-dot--end {
    background: transparent;
    border: 3px solid var(--yellow);
  }

  .tl-line-seg {
    width: 2px;
    background: #2a2a2a;
    flex: 1;
    min-height: 2rem;
    margin: 0.4rem 0;
  }

  .tl-body { padding-bottom: 2.25rem; }
  .tl-item--last .tl-body { padding-bottom: 0; }

  .tl-title {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', 'Arial Narrow', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    padding-top: 0.05rem;
  }

  .tl-desc {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #aaa;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Responsive ---- */
  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .prose-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.25rem; }
    .steps-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .rider-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
    .faq-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
    .faq-sidebar { position: static; }
    .details-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .section { padding: 3.5rem 1.25rem; }
    .page-hero { padding: 3rem 1.25rem; }
    .steps-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .rider-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .details-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .tl-item { grid-template-columns: 62px 26px 1fr; gap: 0 0.85rem; }
    .tl-hr { font-size: 1.2rem; }
  }
</style>
